12.19.24  4:19 am   hi bill. i am currently wondering why are things like fashion or music or movies considered "vintage" or "retro" once they get to a certain age, but never people? i am the same age as some of the things being called "vintage", and yet somehow i am not also vintage, just a young person. seems like a paradox to me, or something like that

      that's because 'vintage' means more than just age. it also means 'we are probably talking about fashion or those other things you mentioned'. just like "kind regards" means more than just "this is the end of the message", it also means "you and i don't know each other very well and are not friends on a close personal basis"

12.18.24  8:25 pm   please help, everytime I write a song the instrumental is okay and great and fantastic but the instant I start putting vocals in I just hate it, everything about it (even though most people say what im doing good i just hear those little inconsistencies that just stand out so much to me) any advice?

      if you have a song with words and singing, sometimes it helps to get the vocal recorded first. although first first you have to put down some instruments to be able to sing over, then record the vocal, then go back and do the instruments good. if you really do the whole instrumental arrangement first, then there might not be any room for vocals
